    correctAnswer:"A lawyer (consumer courts allow self-representation)",
    difficulty:"medium",
    explanation:"One key feature of consumer courts is that consumers do not need a lawyer — they can represent themselves, making the system accessible. This reduces the cost and intimidation of seeking legal redressal.",
    solutionSteps:["Consumer courts: simple procedure","No mandatory lawyer","Consumer can appear personally","Makes justice accessible to common people"],
